# Update Documentation After Every Change

After completing ANY implementation work (feature, bugfix, refactor, or config change), update the relevant project documentation before considering the task done.

## What to Update

1. **`TODO.md`** — Check off completed tasks; update phase status when a phase completes.
2. **`docs/quality.md`** — Update grades for domains you touched (Data pipeline, Signals & backtest, Web dashboard).
3. **`specs/README.md`** — Update verification status for affected specs.
4. **`specs/{system}.md`** — Reconcile spec with code; note deviations in Design Decisions.
5. **`docs/plans/active/`** — Update ExecPlan progress or move completed plans to `docs/plans/completed/`.

## Domain → spec mapping

| You changed | Update |
| :--- | :--- |
| `scripts/clean_bbg_export.py`, `data/processed/` | `specs/data-pipeline.md`, quality row **Data pipeline** |
| `scripts/phase1_build.py`, `web/public/data/phase1.json` | `specs/signals-backtest.md`, quality row **Signals & backtest** |
| `web/src/**`, `web/public/**` | `specs/web-dashboard.md`, quality row **Web dashboard** |

**Code changes without doc updates are incomplete work.**
